shared_text:
Nebraska School Activities Association
September 7 at 2:02 PM ·

NSAA Membership Monday: Bayard Public Schools

Home of the Tigers, Bayard is located in District 6 and offers 15 sports and activities. Bayard created the “LEAD Team” which is comprised of student leaders who meet with their peers and listen to their concerns, and then share and advocate for the students to the administration. A member of the student body also serves as the School Board student representative as well as a liaison between the Board of Education and the student body. The Tigers have won 8 NSAA State Championships in three sports.

September 1 at 12:02 AM ·

Jack Kildow, a senior at Bayard High School, has been named Nspire Today!’s Male Athlete of the Week, sponsored by Kristy Culek Agency, LLC-American Family Insurance.

Para-Educator and Bus Driver Opportunities

Bayard Public Schools is now accepting applications for the positions of para-educator and bus driver for the 2020-2021 school term. The school district has excellent educational and extra-curricular facilities. Interested candidates, please visit https://bayardpublicschools.tedk12.com/hire/index.aspx to complete an application form and obtain additional information. Bayard Public Schools is an equal opportunity employer. Positions subject to a veterans preference. The positions will remain open until filled.

Bayard Public Schools Parents/Guardians,

We need your help with planning for re-opening our school.

We are working with the Nebraska Association of School Boards to survey parents to inform planning for re-opening our schools. We need your insights in order to work towards a quality plan for our community.

Please take about 5 minutes of your time to complete the survey for each of your children who will be enrolled in the district during the 2020-2021 school year.

The deadline to complete the survey is Sunday at midnight.

Thank you in advance for your time and for sharing your perspectives.

Here is the link to the parent survey:

https://nasb.sjc1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6lrEb1pjFTihTHT

post_text:
Elementary Teacher (Grades 4-6 Science and Math Focus Preferred)

Coaching/Extra Duty Opportunities Available

Full Family Insurance Provided

Bayard Public Schools is now accepting applications for the position of Elementary Teacher (Grades 4-6 Science and Math Focus Preferred) for the 2020-2021 school term. Qualified candidates must be eligible for a Nebraska Teaching Certificate and hold an appropriate endorsement. Bayard is a Class C2 school in scenic Western Nebraska. The school district has excellent educational and extra-curricular facilities. Interested candidates, please visit www.bayardpublicschools.org to submit an application electronically. The position is subject to a veterans preference. Bayard is an equal opportunity employer. The position will remain open until filled.

Job Opening: Secondary Math Teacher

Coaching/Extra Duty Opportunities Available

Full Family Insurance Provided

Bayard Public Schools is now accepting applications for the position of Secondary Math Teacher for the 2020-2021 school term. Qualified candidates must be eligible for a Nebraska Teaching Certificate and hold an appropriate endorsement. Bayard is a Class C2 school in scenic Western Nebraska. The school district has excellent educational and extra-curricular facilities. Interested candidates, please visit http://ow.ly/KrWd50zmTnL to submit an application electronically. The position is subject to a veterans preference. Bayard is an equal opportunity employer. The position will remain open until filled.

post_text:
Hey families! We know we are working through a lot of issues with trying to move to an online education platform. Some iPads are still trying to download zoom, and the internet can be spotty. Please remember if you are lacking internet access, we ask that you first contact Charter/Spectrum (866-874-2389) or Allo communications (877-935-6005) who are offering free wifi for students.
If those solutions do not apply to you, please contact Candace Smith (candace.smith@bayardtigers.org).

We will keep working at getting everyone connected, please stay patient and don't stress. This week is for reconnecting with our students (we have missed you!) and working out the kinks. Thank you for all of your dedication and support, we will continue to work through this transition together!
text:

We will keep working at getting everyone connected, please stay patient and don't stress. This week is for reconnecting with our students (we have missed you!) and working out the kinks. Thank you for all of your dedication and support, we will continue to work through this transition together!

post_text:
Pathfinders along with Extension Educator Tammie Ostdiek will begin a unit of garden study called Learn, Grow, Eat & Go! Over the next 6 weeks, starting on Wednesday March 4th, your child will use this science program to learn about plants—why they are important to us, and how to give plants what they need. While learning how to provide for plants’ needs, the students will also learn how plants provide for our needs. The lessons will use math, science, language arts, health, and social studies concepts to help students understand how plants help us live, grow, learn, and play.

Class time is from 4:30 to 5:30 Wednesday Afternoons running March 4th - April 8th. The class is designed for students age 8 and over.

post_text:
Dear Parents and Students,

The district is monitoring the developing information related to the spread of COVID-19 (commonly referred to as the coronavirus). To date, the district is unaware of any native cases of COVID-19 being reported in our state. However, the district has reviewed its relevant policies and procedures and is confident that it is prepared to respond to any outbreak of communicable disease that may occur. Should this situation interfere with the district’s ordinary operations or schedule, you will be provided notice in the customary fashion.

We encourage you to remain informed about the spread of the coronavirus, and would recommend that you visit the website for the Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services, http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx for further information as it develops. We would also encourage you to use this opportunity to remind your students of the importance of getting rest and washing hands, especially during cold and flu season.

Dr. Travis Miller
Superintendent of Schools

Bayard Public Schools
February 24 at 4:06 PM ·

The Pathfinder after school program line-up for this week:
Monday 2/24
Lego Club: Marble Mazes
Boy's Club: Roll a Story is a fun narrative writing, in which students roll dice to determine their character, setting, and conflict.
Girl's Club: Eggxperiments - STEAM activities using eggs
Tuesday 2/25
Cooking Club: Tortilla Roll Ups
Science Club: Building Atoms
STEAM Club: Salt Circuit
Sports Club 3rd through 6th grade
Wednesday 2/26
Cooking: Tortilla Roll Ups
Sports: Kindergarten through 3rd Grade
Sign Language Club
Venture Lab: In Prototyping, students create a basic prototype that solves a problem or fills a need identified in Market Research, use a questionnaire to collect primary market research, and make one iteration to their prototype based on feedback.
Thursday 2/27
4-H night: Congratulations to our new officers. President - Reice Carter, Vice President - Charles Hirsch, Secretary - Andrew Miller, Treasures - Cruz Trevino, and Sergeant at Arms - Mercedez Trevino. This will be the first meeting that they run.
Friday: 2/28 Pick two clubs
Computes, Sports, Legos, Coloring, Be Kind

Pathfinder Program for Thursday 2-13:
4-H Day: Students will be giving speeches about what Leadership Roles they would like in our 4-H club. We are looking for President, Vice-President, Secretary, Treasurer, and Pledge Leader. Then the students will continue working on their projects. These include knitting, name art, mosaic, cooking 101, and youth in motion.

Pathfinder After School Clubs Wednesday Schedule: Wednesday 2-12
Cooking Club - Valentine's Cookies
Sign Language
Sports: Kindergarten - 3rd grade
Venture Lab Entrepreneurial Learning - Customer Observation begins with a preview of the terms “market” and “research.” Students play a game to match pictures of customers to products and discuss how markets are made up of people. They then observe people in different scenarios and discuss the challenges they face or needs they have and come up with products that people would purchase.
